Definition: smoothly agreeable and courteous with a degree of sophistication
Example: he was too politic to quarrel with so important a personage; the manager pacified the customer with a smooth apology for the error
Synonyms: smooth, noun, attribute, smoothness, suave, suaveness, suavity, bland, blandness, smoothly, agreeable, and, courteous, with, a, degree, of, sophistication, he, was, too, to, quarrel, so, important, personage, the, manager, pacified, customer, apology, for, error
Category: adj.all
